- Impact factor over ten is considered high, signifying significant influence and prestige in their field;
- NIH refers to the National Institutes of Health, a major funder of biomedical research in the United States;
- Citations are a measure of the influence and importance of scholarly work, akin to stars shining in the night sky.

- Randomized controlled trials are a type of study design where participants are randomly assigned to different groups to compare the effects of an intervention; 
- 'Downloaded' articles refer to those that have been accessed for downloading by researchers; 
- The clinical relevance score indicates how pertinent the study findings are to clinical practice.
